gov.nasa.worldwind.formats.shapefile

Class ShapefileRecordPolyline

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nasa.worldwind.formats.shapefile.ShapefileRecord
      • gov.nasa.worldwind.formats.shapefile.ShapefileRecordPolyline
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ShapefileRecordPolygon

    public class ShapefileRecordPolyline
extends ShapefileRecord
    Represents a Shapefile record with a polyline shape type. Polyline shapes represent an connected sequence of two or more x,y coordinate pairs. Polyline shapes may contain multiple parts, where each part is an independent connected sequence of two or more points.

    Polylines may have optional z-coordinates or m-coordinates that accompany each coordinate pair. If a Polyline has z-coordinates, then getZValues() returns a non-null array of values. If a Polyline has m-coordinates, then getMValues() returns a non-null array of values.

      • getBoundingRectangle

        public double[] getBoundingRectangle()
        Returns a four-element array containing the record's bounding rectangle, or null if record parsing failed. The returned array is ordered as follows: minimum Y, maximum Y, minimum X, and maximum X. If the Shapefile's coordinate system is geographic, the elements can be interpreted as angular degrees in the order minimum latitude, maximum latitude, minimum longitude, and maximum longitude.
        Returns:
        the record's bounding rectangle, or null to denote the record parsing failed.
